Code,        Status,                                           Why?
"new HashMap<String, Integer>()",   Valid (Old),Redundant.    You repeat yourself.
new HashMap<>(),  Valid (Best),                               Uses Type Inference. Clean and safe.
new HashMap(),    Valid (Bad),                                Raw Type. loses type safety guarantees.

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Syntax,              Meaning
<>,"The Labels:"    "Make sure this box only holds Strings and Integers."""
(),"The Action:"    "Build the box now using default settings."""
(100),"The Action:" "Build the box now, but make it big enough for 100 items."""

